<p>
<h2>The most important part of a software bug's life is triage.</h2>
</p>

<p>
Triage is more than just filing a bug in the right category; it's about clarifying,
simplifying and reproducing the challenges our users face, about getting a bug from 
an incident reported by a user to an understood problem ready for an enginering
decision.
</p>

<p>
Mozilla sees dozens or hundreds of new bugs every day, but if you can spare a few
minutes of your day you can help us stay on top of them. Sign up below; enter your
name, Bugzilla email address, and a number of bugs we can send you.  Once a week,
five days a week or every day, we'll send you an email with links to new issues
our community is facing, so you can help get them to the right place.
</p>


